fontTheory.description: A typography system strictly using only the fonts extracted from the PDF: d3_f1, d3_f2, d3_f5, d3_f4, d3_f3. Following Derrida's philosophy of deconstruction, we've preserved the original typography without introducing external elements.
fontTheory.readability: The fonts chosen maintain a consistent style throughout the design, enhancing readability by providing a clear visual hierarchy.
fontTheory.hierarchy: The hierarchy is established through font sizes, weights, and styles. Headings in d3_f1 are bold and prominent, while body text in d3_f2 is regular for easy reading. Titles and subtitles in d3_f3 are distinct but complementary to the headings. Monospace text in d3_f1 is used for code snippets, ensuring a clear differentiation from regular text.
fontTheory.fontPairings: The font pairings focus on creating a harmonious blend within the constraints of the extracted fonts. While each font serves a specific purpose, they work together to create a cohesive and structured typographic system.
